Alysa and Anthony did their partying right 👏🏼✨

The best way to get a wild dance floor all night long and epic photos of your guests is to actually be dancing with them! Truly, allll your friends and fam will follow your lead. If they see you going wild on the dance floor all night, they will join 🙌🏼 If you’re mingling off the dance floor most of the night, you may have a less rowdy reception!

When you dance together throughout the night, you’ll, of course, get so many more amazing photos of the two of you, but also of all your loved ones around you!

Not dancing together again after your first dance honestly happens sooo often 🥺 but if you want your party animal guests to have the best time, make sure to get out there with them! 💃🏽 

Share with the person who you know will be on the dance floor alllll night long 🪩🕺🤩

Big wedding party energyyy 🎉

Make your people feel special by:

🫶🏼 Including them in the schedule/timeline process! Everyone just wants to know what’s going on ahead of time so they can prepare. So often, the wedding party is never told much more than “arrive at this time.” Give them the run down of the day a few weeks before, so they can get even more excited, ask questions ahead of time, and help when needed!

🎁 Gifts! Doesn’t need to be anything crazy expensive - even a handwritten card or a printed photo thanking your people for their love and support will go a long way! Bonus points if you save the gifts for when your photographer arrives. It’s always so cute seeing reactions as they open gifts or read cards!

👯‍♀️ Ask for input! A lot of friends and family have been a part of weddings before and can give you insight, support, or fun new ideas! 💕

If you love these photos or found this post helpful, please save it for inspo while planning! 🤩

Gentle reminder that you don’t need to have it all figured out by January 1st 🗓️ 

If you haven’t set a single goal or haven’t had time to decompress from 2022, that’s OKAY!

If you don’t know what your word of the year is or what each quarter is going to look like, you’re not falling behind.

If you don’t know what you want your life to look like in 2023, you aren’t going to fail in the new year.

Yes, it’s nice to have a plan or a vision and yes, it’s an awesome way to track your success or goals being able to start at the beginning of the year, but if you need time, space, rest, or just a break, you can still have an amazing 2023.

Your year isn’t shot if you don’t have it all together in the next day or two. Jan 1st is ONE of many ways you can game plan, but if your “start” doesn’t look like what everyone else is telling you it needs to look like, trust that it’ll all fall into place.

A few ways to notice some possible focuses for next year as you’re going about your day:

>> Think of where your mind wanders when you’re not working

>> Notice what you’re passionately searching for on TikTok and Instagram during your late night scrolls or breaks in the day (mine has been needle punching and renter friendly decor 🤷🏼‍♀️)

>> Write down your ideas when they come to you in the car or shower, and revisit when you have a fresh mind and can really take action on them

I’d looove to say I have it allllll together and have a full plan for 2023, but I’m still finishing up life in 2022 and giving myself space to dream and grow for next year!

Who knows what it’ll bring - not me (yet!) ☺️✨🫶🏼 Is the new year your big restart or just another day for you?

And with that, the 2022 season comes to an end ✨

This year was magical, amazing, hard at times, and so inspiring. 👏🏼

I did more “life” things this year than ever before with focusing on our wedding, marriage, friendships, family, and travel, and that made all the difference. It got stressful at times, but also gave me so many memories away from the computer screen or camera. A mental reset I’ve been needing. Still clocked in an insane amount of editing hours 🤣 but I experienced so much this year regardless 🙌🏼

Our wedding experience gave me such a fresh perspective on photographing weddings, and I’m so grateful for all the incredible moments I was able to capture of my incredible couples. 2023 is going to be another unreal year with my couples and their meaningful, beautiful wedding days! I can’t wait to celebrate all the love and fun moments to come 🥹 thank you all for choosing me, I’m forever grateful to have this business and can’t wait to see all that’s to come for TKP ✨

I don’t have the mental capacity to wrap up 2022 in 473893 videos (major props to everyone for these recap reels 😅) but honestly, this video captures all the joy and energy I want to bring into 2023 better than anything I could put together 💕 forever my favorite day.

Happy new year! 🎊 let’s make magic in 2023 😍

Did these two fly me out to Santa Fe to photograph them dolled up in the desert and getting spicy in a hot spring?!

Yes, yes they did. 👏🏼

And it just made everything THAT much more special and FUN on their wedding day after adventuring with them in New Mexico 🙌🏼

I looove the connection we build from inquiry to engagement session to wedding day and beyond. That’s why I always encourage my couples to pick the wild ideas they have for their engagement session or to focus on what truly feels like them. ~ Unseen bits from our wedding welcome party! ~

I have so freaking much I still want to share from our wedding, like every little detail and moment – I feel like I could never do it all justice in a few posts, but I have forever to try 😋

We had a lot of family and friends traveling in from all across the country to celebrate our wedding with us, so it felt more special to get the party started with anyone in town the night before! We invited everyone to a local cidery down the road from our venue for some casual hangs, and it was such an amazing way to kick off the weekend!

Around 100 guests joined us throughout the night with a come and go as you please kind of flow! We knew a Friday would be hard for people after work, but it was amazing how many of our guests showed up! 🥹 It was actually really nice to have guests trickle in throughout the night so we could spend time with everyone! We even had some guests who couldn't make it for our wedding still join us on Friday, which meant the world that they made that effort.

@penningsfarmcidery gave us our own private space for a few hours before opening up to the public, so we used that time for handing out welcome bags, enjoying a vegan buffet and open bar, lawn games, and cider flights/tastings! We hired a live band to play out in the field and had 2 really special toasts from both of our brothers to personalize the evening 🫶🏼

We didn't have a wedding party or a formal ceremony processional, so we really didn't need to rehearse much of anything. So, if you're feeling like a rehearsal dinner doesn't fit your vibe – scrap it. Do something that feels more like you. I'm so glad we got to spend quality time with our friends and a family the day before because obviously, our wedding went by so quickly, and it wouldn't have felt 'complete' without getting time to sit down and really see a lot of our guests who traveled in.

I just wish the weekend never had to end, I miss it all so much. There's nothing like being surrounded by so many people who love you and who traveled from all over to celebrate your marriage.

Some may call it naivety, but I just call it an entrepreneurial spirit 🤩

I’ve watched my parents start and grow successful businesses my entire life. And if their passion changed, they pivoted and tried something new. I’ve always been inspired by that “you will always find a way to make it work if you care about it enough” mindset.

I don’t take it lightly that I have parents and the most supportive partner who encouraged me to chase my passions and grow something entirely “me” from the ground up.

I just always had the mindset of “I will make this work,” even if it meant adapting and changing. Trust me, TKP has seen many iterations and changes over the years, and that’s what’s so special about a personal brand. My business has grown so organically with me. Like I’m literal biz besties with my own biz 😋

And while I knew I was risking the security and safety net of a 9 to 5 by not applying for jobs out of college, I could never imagine myself at a desk, with a boss, not allowing my creativity to run free. That gut feeling that I was meant to do my own thing was so clear to me - it would’ve been so unfortunate not to chase that and just try. Have you felt that in yourself, too?

My people have seen that fire, passion, and heart in me and my work since I was 12 years old with a camera glued to my hand. You, my friend, are the reason I keep going.

If anyone is telling you not to chase your dreams, that you’re not good enough, or that it’s too risky or not possible to “make it,” please know that your success will quiet their lack of belief in you.

There are so many lives waiting to be impacted by your unique talents and heart. What a disservice to not give them a chance to experience all that you are and can do because you’re stuck believing you’re not good enough. You’re so much more than that.

You’re so capable, and you will make it work if your drive and passion outweigh your fear. 👏🏼 cheering you on every step of the way.

You will always love looking at your photos on your phone and of course, you’ll have your faves that you’ll reshare for birthdays and anniversaries, but there are so many special little moments and details that deserve to be honored in the same way.

An album is a curated overview of the story of your day for you to relive and share for years to come 🥹 

👉🏼 It’s for when friends and family come over and want to see the highlights without looking through hundreds of photos on a screen.

👉🏼 It’s for future children and grandchildren to point at and see their family tree and the people who helped shape their parents into who they are.

👉🏼 It’s to help take you two back to the emotions and joy of your day.

Artistically choosing the images that best tell that story, so your love and marriage can be romanticized in the way they deserve is key 👌🏼 I just love this perfect way to wrap up your wedding day, it’s so surreal to be able to hold it in your hands.

What’s your take? Are you an album type or do you want to keep it digital? 💕

Imagine your best friend NOT being at your wedding 😩

My furbaby loving couples know what I mean!! Here are some pet tips for your wedding day!

🐶 Hire a dog walker, not just a friend who likes dogs! A professional dog walker knows how to manage pets with all the craziness of a wedding day!

🧸 Have them bring toys, treats, water, bags, and a nice neutral colored leash!

🤞🏼Have your pets arrive at least 15-20 minutes or more before we need them for photos to help them acclimate to a new area. They can get all the sniffing and potty breaks out of the way before we need them for photos.

😴 Have a going home plan for your pups! Make sure there’s a trusted person (who doesn’t need to be in photos) getting them back home safely!

💕 Maintain expectations with your pet! Of course, we will do everything we can to get the perfect shot with them looking at the camera, but all furbabies are different! Being in a new environment with all new stimulations can sometimes cause animals to act totally different than what we’d expect of them, and that’s NORMAL!

👉🏼 If they’re not feeling it at the moment, we can take a little break and have them rejoin later in the portrait time.

🥰 Overall, letting your pet be themselves whether that’s calm, playful, or anything in between is perfect – it’ll feel more genuine to not force them to pose or do anything they’re not comfortable with!

🐱 Cute ideas for including them in other parts of the day:
* Walking down the aisle as flower girl or ring bearer
* Custom napkins or drink stirrers with their face
* Signature drink named after them (we had ‘The Crazy Hazy’ for our dog Hazel as our drink)
* A little figurine of them on your wedding cake (so cute if it takes a bite out of the frosting and gets a bit on his nose)
* A little dog/cat treat to-go bar at the end of the night along with late night snacks for the humans!

A few wonderful wedding day pet attendants I highly recommend 👏🏼 @smile_n_wag @weddingpuptials @fureveralways

Save this post for your own wedding plans and share with another furbaby-obsessed friend!

Your day is made up of so many little moments and emotions. Yes, we’ll capture stunning portraits and all the beautiful details – that’s a given 👏🏼

But the moments that just happen – the ones you really can’t plan for 👉🏼 the laughter, tears, and just casual hangs in between the timeline ‘must-do’s’ are the memories you’re going to cherish most.

It’s the way your dad holds back tears when he sees you at your first look.

The way your mom is beaming at her beautiful daughter getting ready for the day.

Your besties all taking selfies and hyping each other up.

The endless beer and mimosas flowing all morning. 🥂 

It’s snacking on goldfish in your robe while you’re waiting to get dressed.

It’s all the quiet and loud moments that culminate into the full story of your day. Where I can be a fly on the wall and witness everything unfold.

I live for this ebb and flow of emotion in your day, and getting ready in the morning is where so much of that happens. It may feel like these aren’t important to capture, but once you see them in your gallery, you’ll realize how special they truly are.

I literally couldn’t squeeze enough of these precious little moments from Hannah and Andrew’s morning into this post, hahah.

I just love capturing it all, and that’s why I work with a team of 3 to be in multiple places at once. We truly want to be your eyes throughout the day so you can just soak it in, live it all up in the moment, and then relive it for years to come. 🫶🏼

Save this post to your wedding planning folder 🙌🏼 these candid moments are everything!

Just a little full circle moment from my first few years as a wedding photographer allll the way to getting married at @therealpioneerfarm last summer 🥹

I remember the bride told me “they don’t cut diamonds like this anymore.” And I knew at that moment that it was exactly what I would want someday.

Years later, my mom passed down my great grandmother’s diamond, and right when I saw it, I could tell it was the same - vintage and hand cut. It has this jaggedy texture inside that reflects light so beautifully.

I remembered that gorgeous ring from 2018 that we photographed at my favorite venue, and it all clicked! 💍 I knew we had to head to Warwick, NY see if it was a perfect fit for our weekend.

Pioneer Farm was the only venue we visited (my job set me up pretty well to already know what I liked and didn’t like 😋), and it hit the nail on the head for our dreamy wedding weekend!

When will I stop melting over our wedding?! Hmm pretty much never 🤷🏼‍♀️😋

What else would you like to know about our wedding experience? Ask away, I’ll be sure to share! ✨

"We're pretty awkward in front of the camera, we def need all the help we can get"

Does this sound like you? Considering I hear this from mosttt of my couples when they first reach out, I know it's a pretty common fear!

Buuut I mean.. just take a sec and look at the photos on my blog and Instagram again. Just about every single one of those couples felt the same when they reached out. And look at them - natural and cute af ;)

It's MY job to get you comfortable in front of the camera. Your job is to just be willing and open to go with it and have a great time.

👏🏼 I promise, I'll take care of the rest.

That's everythinggg I've built my movement-based posing method around – helping you two feel like yourselves, so your photos reflect your love and real personalities.

Start with a location that means something to you, whether it's a vibe you love, a special place to your love story, or a location that allows you to DO something you enjoy.

Then, add an activity or props – beers at your fave beer garden, pizza picnic overlooking the view on your fave hike, making coffee in your kitchen, roller skating, getting ice cream, snuggling your pup, long boarding on the rooftop of your apartment, hanging in your hammock, and the list goes on.

Doing an activity takes your mind off of the fact that we're taking pictures and lets you focus on something that already feels natural to you.

And then pair it with clothing that makes sense! No need to bust out the heels on a hike or wear the tightest dress if you prefer to breathe.

I don't want you to have to worry about feeling uncomfy if your outfit instead of focusing on each other.

If you're self conscious about your arms, let's skip the spaghetti straps and find a cute flowy top. If you want to show off your legs, a dress with a slit could be perfect! If you literally wear your fave denim daily, no need to buy new jeans!

I’ll be here to help you choose your session details with intention – where we go, what we do, and how we do it. The rest will fall into place perfectly!

Calling all nontraditional couples 💕 this one’s for you!

If you’re a more private couple who wants to express your feelings without all eyes on you, personal vows after your first look might just be for you 📖 

Not only do you feel waaay more relaxed to really get emotional and share inside jokes, but also you can take extra time to slow down, soak it in, and write as much as you want. No ceremony time constraints to stress about!

And one of the biggest reasons I’m hearing from my couples opting for private vows is simply that they want a shorter ceremony! Not a bad reason at all since that means more cocktail hour and party time 👏🏼🎉

Have you considered private vows? Any thoughts for or against them?! 🫶🏼 lmk!! I love the intimacy and sweetness of these moments 🥹

Living for seeing this excitement in my couples as they enter new chapters 🥲

Whether it’s an engagement, wedding, bby in the way, anniversary, birthday, or just because - it’s worth celebrating and remembering. These photos get more and more special with time. 🫶🏼

It doesn’t matter if you take pictures on your phone, a polaroid, a film camera from your grandpa, the camcorder your parents used with you as a kiddo, or a photoshoot with a professional photographer, just take the pics, please. ✨

When it comes to your memories, you’re just going to be glad you have them documented years from now.

So many posts in bridal Facebook groups feeling torn on the dream dress. I was there, I remember losing sleep over the dresses I loved.

And in the end, I picked what I felt beautiful in, and it was perfect. But it would’ve also been perfect had I picked any others, because it was our wedding day and I couldn’t go wrong.

The most helpful piece of advice Shawn gave me when I’d get stressed over decisions was to recognize that you literally cannot and will not find the world’s best option when it comes to decor, vendors, outfits, etc.

There’s no possible way to find the all time best because that literally doesn’t exist. It’s completely subjective. What I think is the perfect dress could be someone’s nightmare dress. What I love for decor and design, someone else would never choose. What we loved for food, music, media, venue, etc. could be a dream to us and a hard no for someone else. That’s why it’s YOUR wedding.

When I couldn’t make up my mind, he helped me narrow it down to the top three, and from there - just pick. Every option is a good option at that point, every vendor had amazing reviews in your top three, and whatever the decision was - it would be amazing. And guess what? It was - every one of our vendors crushed it and our wedding came together beautifully imo 👏🏼

Your wedding is never about having the best, most iconic, top in the world of anything. It’s about having each other and a really freaking good time, and with that, you can’t lose. 🫶🏼

The one constant I've held close as a wedding photographer is this:

Focus on the moments

When the wedding industry changes by the day, editing styles adapt over the years, and there's new photography gear to test, it's easy to fall into trends and changes. And some of it is truly creatively fulfilling, and I'm game to play when it feels right, but I've built my business and style on this pillar: real moments > fake moments.

I scrolled 7 years back into my gallery archives to double check if my day one approach matched my day 2500+ approach, and I'm proud to say I haven’t swayed from that. While my skill, style, and experience have all grown like wildflowers, at the core, I've always shown up to shoot what happens throughout the day – the messy and magical.

It sounds like a no brainer.. like, doesn't everyone take candids? Honestly, no. Not everyone focuses on the candids, and that's okay – that may not be their approach and vibe. There's a photographer out there for everyone. My couples and my people just get it.

For me, the wilder the better – the more unhinged, real, and emotional you get with your people, the more beautiful the gallery becomes. Just because I try to avoid completely faking moments doesn't mean your photos won't be stunning, it just means I'm not killing real moments for the sake of absolute perfection.

Like if you're hugging your mom and the lighting isn't ideal, I can work with that. If the space is a mess because you've been getting ready since 6am, I'll still come through with gorgeous photos. Your loved ones hugging, your uncle shoving his face at cocktail hour, your cousins screaming on the dance floor, your besties hyping you up, champagne popping, cake half eaten, tears from grandma during the ceremony. Of course we'll take stunning sunset portraits that show off your love, but I also want to catch you breaking it tf down on the dance floor right after! :)

We won't redo a real moment, act like anything you're not, or stand in weird poses. I want your photos to reflect you two in love, having an incredible day with your people.

My artful approach to storytelling is simply showing off the realness right in front of me.

You? You’ve been tucked away for about 30 - 45 minutes before your ceremony to avoid being seen and to take a break from photos! Most of my couples enjoy a bite of food, get excited with their wedding party, or just take a breather alone with their spouse-to-be!

Remember, we just rolled through getting ready into your first look, couples photos, wedding party, and family photos – it’s a lot up front so you can just relax after the ceremony and make it to cocktail hour! This time to just chill before the realll party gets started is so necessary!

Sometimes it’s your venue or officiant’s call on where they need you during that time – they may have to do a quick rehearsal, have you sign your marriage license, or go over some housekeeping before you walk down the aisle.

Me? I’m photographing the ceremony display and set ups before guests have touched anything! I’m capturing candids and casual group photos whenever possible. My assistant may be with you capturing candids if you request it – some couples want some time away from the camera while others love those casual moments!

These little breaks and buffers I build into your timeline are key to creating a seamless, stress-free wedding day! Any timeline questions? Hit me with them!

Short, sweet, and personal af – just how I love ceremonies!

The keyyy to keeping your guests from snoring, looking at their phone, or talking during your ceremony is to:

💕 Invite guests who have so much love for you! People who genuinely care about you and your relationship actually do love getting to see these special moments.

🤵 Consider someone special to officiate! Your officiant sets the tone and vibe of your ceremony whether it’s 15 minutes or an hour. Someone who knows you two well, has great public presence and speaking skills, and can get to the point will keep the energy high! A good mix of funny stories and sweet sentiments create a dynamic and engaging storyline!

👀 Focus on each other AND your guests. Hold hands, come closer to each other, look into each others eyes, and also look out toward everyone else a few times. It brings some of the most genuine smiles and reactions when you get a peek at your loved ones looking back at you! Also, then not all of your photos are just of your profiles - adds some variety!

📝 Although your vows are for you, try to keep them from being one long inside joke that only you two understand! Your guests want to get a sense of your love, banter, personalities, etc. We had so many guests tell us how much they loved learning about us through our officiants’ words and our personal vows - I just thought that was so sweet that they actually listened 🤣

🎤 Make sure the mic and speakers can reach everyone. I’ve seen sooo many ceremonies where nobody beyond the 2nd row can hear a thing. Literally, say it louder for the people in the back 👋🏼

👏🏼 Don’t drag it on if you don’t want to! You don’t NEED to have any guest speakers, sand ceremonies, extra traditions, etc. if it’s not something you care about!

💋 Change what doesn’t fit your personalities. We personally changed “You may now kiss the bride” to “You may now kiss each other.” Just felt more modern for us.

Cheer, party, kiss down the aisle and then go freaking celebrate!!!

On April 10, 2020 while the house was still in the remodeling phase (also during covid) he decorated the house with rose petals, candles on ladders, a heater, a table with a meal, etc. He had a hidden camera set up to catch everything on camera (my only request was to have it filmed/photographed). When we walked in I said, “Wow if this is what you do for my birthday, I can only imagine what you are going to do when you propose!” I was so clueless lol. We got up to dance and he got on one knee. It was magical.” How incredible is that?! A memorable moment in such a special place!! 🏠

🙌🏼 Our Save the Dates planned our wedding!!

Okay, more specifically, our incredibly talented stationery designer, Summit & Sage, designed a save the date that set the entire tone for our wedding! 

Pulled from the email archives, here’s what I brain dumped to her when I inquired:

📧 “I envision our invitation/stationery to be a really fun, beatuiful introduction for the feeling of our weekend! Colors, fonts, style... I don’t even kind of know. I want to say the vibes right now are kind of festival weekend, glamping, nature-focused, whimsical, natural, fun, laidback, and relaxed.” And she turned that mess into a literal wedding brand!

We revised and finalized the vibiest postcard save the dates that screamed laidback summer festival. The admission ticket-inspired rsvp card in the invites brought it homeee 🎟️ 

The color palette, fonts, logo, and every detail later played into our full wedding day design with everything below fully customized to match the theme:

	•	Invitation suite (we used recycled & tree-free paper with a plantable seed paper belly band)
	•	Wedding website
	•	Camp-style enamel mugs with macramé wine charm name tags
	•	Mug & late night snack wall (for popcorn and taco bell burritos, of course)
	•	Welcome tote bags for hotel guests
	•	Welcome sign
	•	Ceremony signs
	•	Vow books & officiant book
	•	Signature drink signs
	•	Name place cards
	•	Phone guestbook sign
	•	Temporary tattoo sheets (designs inspired by the custom map from our invitations!)
	•	Tri-Fold table number/menu/message to our guests

👌🏼 Using the same design elements created a cohesive experience where everything tied together throughout the weekend!

My genuine response after seeing the Save the Date design:

“ALEX!!!!!!! HOLY SHIIIIIT! I seriously adore these more than words can say! SUCH A FREAKING VIBE! Thank you for taking my brain mush and turning it into magic, as always!! Like wowowowowow this is just our save the date?! Invites are going to be next level, AH!!”

Was I a little extra when it comes to the details?! Yep. It’s the only way I know how to be.

Kimi & Greg wedding-ed so hard and truly did it right 🙌🏼 Here’s how:

1️⃣ Full trust in their vendors: They mentioned so many times throughout the day that they fully trusted my vision and decisions. They were down for anything and trusted my experience every step of the way. This made for such a fun and laidback day since they let their vendor team take care of the details. This let them just BE at their wedding instead of hosting and running it. Choosing vendors who you have full trust in is key for a stress-free day. We’ve got you. 🥹👏🏼

2️⃣ They let the plan play out: Over a year of planning had finally arrived and they fully embraced the “whatever happens, happens” mindset. There’s nothing left to micromanage or stress about when you’re fully present in the real moments with loved ones instead of worrying about every little detail. All the hard work, decisions, and planning was done, it was time to see it all come together and enjoy it!

3️⃣ Comfy shoes: Can’t even tell you how many couples end up frustrated simply because they’re uncomfortable in their attire (itchy dress/suit, too tight, painful heels, veil pulling hair, etc.). Kimi wore sneakers all day and she said it was the best decision ever (I did the same for our wedding and totally agree)! Choose comfy shoes so you can actually dance all night long. Those dance floor memories are more important than a detail photo of fancy shoes that make your toes go numb (even if you wear heels.. always get the sneakers, too)!

4️⃣ Made it meaningful: the special touches will be remembered years from now. At the bar, K & G put childhood photos from when they first met as a 9-year-old footballer and a 6-year-old cheerleader along with their trophies! They included pictures of their dogs on the napkins, an Eagles ice sculpture at cocktail hour, a close friend officiated, Kimi dedicated her bouquet to her mom, they chose a meaningful donation over favors, and so many more special details that will stick with everyone for years to come!

Their day was built on trust and so much love, and it was a dream to photograph!

Working on London and Neil’s heirloom wedding album has me reminiscing on their colorful Haldi ceremony ✨ 

Haldi – meaning turmeric in Hindi – is a traditional celebration symbolizing the start of a prosperous new life together!

💛 This ritual is meant to cleanse, protect, bring good fortune, good luck, and relaxation to the couple before their celebration begins!

Friends and family take turns applying a tumeric paste to the couple, and as you’ll see, nowhere is off limits! 🤣 It was such a special tradition to witness and document. Couldn’t be more obsessed with how these pictures turned out!

With you every step of the way 🤍

So you want to bring your little furry besties to the wedding?! Here’s how you can make it happen:

→ Hire a pro doggy walker - it’ll make pick up and drop off way less stressful, and they’re trained in helping get your dog’s attention for photos! win-win 🙌🏼

→ Plan to have your dog arrive when your portraits start, so they can sniff around, get settled, and go to the bathroom! We’ll have them join in on your portraits midway through and for the first few minutes of wedding party photos if you want to include them with the whole group!

→ Are they staying for your ceremony? Bring a nice leash (instead of the neon colored ones we all usually have!) and add a floral collar necklace from your florist to match the wedding vibes! So cute for pictures!

Whether they manage to hold it together for a bunch of photos or they go absolutely wild the whole time, you’ll honestly just be so happy to see their cute happy faces on your big day! Doesn’t need to be a long time, just a good time! 🎉🐾
